Package: RedoxRRI
Type: Package
Title: Holobiont Redox Resilience Index for Integrative Stress Biology
Version: 0.99.3
Authors@R: c(person("Mitra", "Ghotbi", email = "mitra.ghotbi@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9185-9993")), person("Marjan", "Ghotbi", email = "ghotbi.marjan@gmail.com", role = "ctb", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4655-6445")))
Description: Provides tools to compute the Redox Resilience Index (RRI), a
    composite metric designed to quantify holobiont-level resilience in
    soil–plant–microbiome systems. The framework integrates plant
    physiological traits, soil redox indicators, and microbial community
    features into a unified analytical pipeline. Multivariate indicators
    from each domain are reduced to normalized latent variables using
    dimension-reduction techniques such as principal component analysis,
    factor analysis, nonlinear embeddings, or network-based approaches.
    These domain-specific scores are then combined into an interpretable
    composite index representing system-level redox stability and recovery
    capacity. The package supports both snapshot and temporal experimental
    designs and includes simulated datasets for illustration, benchmarking,
    and testing.
